# 3) Logout (POST + CSRF)

Your logout needs a CSRF token as well. Easiest is to recycle the token from `/auth/login` again.

```bash
logout_with() {
  local jar="$1"
  local token; token="$(get_csrf "$jar")"
  curl -sS -b "$jar" -c "$jar" -X POST "$BASE/auth/logout" \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded' \
    --data-urlencode "csrf_token=${token}" \
    -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}\n'
}

logout_user()  { logout_with "$USER_JAR"; }
logout_admin() { logout_with "$ADMIN_JAR"; }
```

